@startuml sequence_service_data_flow
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Service Management — Data Flow (Grid, Calendar, History)

actor User
participant "WorkOrdersComponent" as WO
participant "Kendo Grid" as Grid
participant "Kendo Scheduler" as Sched
participant "REST API" as API
database "SQL Server" as DB

== List View — Server-Side Grid ==
User -> WO: Navigate to /service
WO -> Grid: Initialize with pageSize=20
Grid -> API: GET /work-orders?skip=0&take=20
API -> DB: SELECT TOP 20\nWHERE OrgId = @OrgId
DB --> API: workOrders[], totalCount
API --> Grid: { data, total }
Grid --> User: Render paginated grid

User -> Grid: Click column header (sort)
Grid -> API: GET /work-orders?skip=0&take=20&sort=priority-desc
API --> Grid: sorted results

User -> Grid: Click next page
Grid -> API: GET /work-orders?skip=20&take=20
API --> Grid: page 2 results

== Calendar View — Kendo Scheduler ==
User -> WO: Switch to calendar tab
WO -> Sched: Initialize with selectedDate
Sched -> API: GET /work-orders/calendar\n?start=2026-04-01&end=2026-04-30
API -> DB: SELECT WHERE RequestedDate\nBETWEEN @start AND @end
DB --> API: calendarEvents[]
API --> Sched: [{id, title, start, end, color}]
Sched --> User: Render month view

== Work Order Detail + History ==
User -> Grid: Click row
WO -> API: GET /work-orders/{id}
API -> DB: SELECT w.*, h.*\nFROM WorkOrders w\nLEFT JOIN History h\n(via EF Include)
DB --> API: workOrder + history[]
API --> WO: { ...workOrder, history: [...] }
WO --> User: Show detail panel\nwith real history

== Status Change — No Optimistic Update ==
User -> WO: Click "Start Work"
WO -> API: PUT /work-orders/{id}/status\n{ status: "InProgress" }
alt API Success
    API --> WO: updated workOrder
    WO --> User: Update UI with new status
else API Failure (422)
    API --> WO: { Error: "Transition not allowed" }
    WO --> User: Show error toast\nUI stays unchanged
end

@enduml
